# 1 

```
sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User (Bash)
    participant NetNS as Network Namespace<br/>(demo-cni-ns)
    participant main as Main CNI Plugin<br/>(/opt/cni/bin/ptp)
    participant ipam as IPAM Plugin<br/>(/opt/cni/bin/host-local)
    participant Disk as Disk DB<br/>(/var/lib/cni/networks/)

    User->>NetNS: 1. ip netns add demo-cni-ns
    Note over User, main: 2. Export Env Vars (CNI_COMMAND=ADD, CNI_NETNS...)
    
    User->>main: 3. Pipe JSON config via stdin
    Note right of main: 4. Reads JSON ("type": "ptp",<br/>"ipam.type": "host-local")
    
    rect rgb(40, 44, 52)
        main->>ipam: 5. Implicitly call host-local plugin
        ipam->>Disk: 6. Find & lock an available IP
        Disk-->>ipam: 7. Return IP (e.g., 10.249.0.2)
        ipam-->>main: 8. Return IP mapping back to ptp
    end

    main->>NetNS: 9. Create interface (eth0) in namespace
    main->>NetNS: 10. Assign IP (10.249.0.2) to eth0
    main-->>User: 11. Print the result JSON to stdout
```

# 2
```
sequenceDiagram
    participant User
    participant Kubelet
    participant API as API Server / Scheduler
    participant CRI as containerd (CRI)
    participant CNI as CNI Plugins

    User->>Kubelet: 1. Write config to /etc/cni/net.d/
    Kubelet->>Kubelet: 2. Detect CNI config, init network state
    Kubelet->>API: 3. Update Node status to Ready (Remove taint)
    
    API->>Kubelet: 4. Assign pending pod "nginx-test" to this node
    
    Kubelet->>CRI: 5. Request to create Pod Sandbox
    CRI->>CNI: 6. Execute CNI binaries (ptp -> host-local)
    
    rect rgb(40, 44, 52)
        Note right of CNI: 7. Network setup (Same flow as Step 3)
    end
    
    CNI-->>CRI: 8. Return assigned IP
    
    CRI-->>Kubelet: 9. Sandbox creation completed successfully
    Kubelet->>API: 10. Update Pod status to Running

```